Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. Library. Performing Arts Special Collections
Title: Bobby Driscoll, James Baskett, and Luana Driscoll in Song Of The South
Description.caption: Above, Brer Bear, Brer Fox and Brer Rabbit journey to the laughing place in Walt Disney's classic live-action/animation fantasy "Song of the South." Below, the trio strolls with Uncle Remus (James Baskett), Johnny (Bobby Driscoll) and Ginny Favors (Luana Patten) through Briar Patch country. Based on Joel Chandler Harris' folk tales of Uncle Remus, the movie is being re-released by Buena Vista, with color by Technicolor.

Name.repository: University of California, Los Angeles. Library. Performing Arts Special Collections
Title: Brer Rabbit and Brer Fox in Song Of The South
Description.caption: Above, Brer Rabbit nails up the entrance to his cottage after deciding to leave his home in the Briar Patch in Walt Disney's classic live-action/animation fantasy "Song of the South." Below, Brer Rabbit cleverly begs Brer Fox not to throw him into the Briar Patch. Based on Joel Chandler Harris' folk tales of Uncle Remus, the movie is being re-released by Buena Vista, with color by Technicolor.

Title: Grace McDonald and dance troupe, the Jivin' Jacks and Jills, performing in Give Out, Sisters
Description.caption: "Give Out, Sisters," a Universal Production.Copyright 1942, Universal Pictures Co., Inc. Permission granted for newspaper and magazine reproductionPrinted in U.S.A.
Description.note: Members of the dance troupe, The Jivin' Jacks and Jills, are seen dancing behind actress Grace McDonald. Dancers possibly appearing in this photograph: Bobby Scheerer, Tommy Rall, Roland Dupree, Joe Geil, Dorothy Babb, Jane McNab, Jean McNab and Dolores Mitchell. Actors Donald O'Connor and Peggy Ryan also perform in this dance routine and may appear in the photograph, as well.
